lead_paragraph: The Continent’s leaders had challenges reaching a consensus on the crisis as humanitarian groups have called the proposed policy a violation of international law.

byline.contributor: Alison Smale contributed reporting from Berlin.

headline.print_headline: Europe Is Weighing Plan to Return Some Migrants
headline.main: European Union Grapples With Plan to Return Migrants From Greece to Turkey

snippet: The Continent’s leaders had challenges reaching a consensus on the crisis as humanitarian groups have called the proposed policy a violation of international law.
abstract: European Union seeks Turkey's consent to return tens of thousands of migrants stalled in Greece there to be processed; proposed agreement, which involves series of controversial concessions to Turkey, is criticized by human rights activists.
